==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acephalocyst
<hw>A*ceph"a*lo*cyst</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'ake`falos</grk> without a head + <grk>ky`stis</grk>
bladder.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A larval entozo⟦oum⟧n in the
form of a subglobular or oval vesicle, or hydatid, filled with fluid,
sometimes found in the tissues of man and the lower animals; -- so
called from the absence of a head or visible organs on the vesicle.
These cysts are the immature stages of certain tapeworms. Also applied
to similar cysts of different origin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acephalocystic</ent>⟦br⟧
